{"build_type":"library","description":"Renders a clone_thread low-op into x86-64 bytes: push rbx/r12/r13; lea rbx,[rip+entry]; in the CONTEXT form the PARENT loads r12=context (from [rbp+ctx_disp]) and r13=context[6] (the per-thread arena block) BEFORE clone, so both survive into the child as copied registers (clone duplicates all regs except rax) -- the child never reads the parent's stack frame, eliminating the post-unwind use-after-free race. clone (syscall 56); branch parent/child on rax. Child (rax 0): mov rdi,r13; call endow (FS host-port leaf, points this thread's FS base at its arena); mov rdi,r12; call entry rbx; thread-exit (60). The no-context form skips the FS step and the r12/r13 loads. Parent pops r13/r12/rbx and stores the child tid into dest. The jnz-over-child displacement is backpatched from the measured child-block length.","module_name":"render-clone-thread-operation-sequence","package_name":"render-clone-thread-operation-sequence","function_definitions":{"render-clone-thread-operation-sequence":{"return_type":"void","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"inst","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"code","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"slotmap","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c1","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c4","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c48","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":48},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c65","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":65},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","varia